The Catalan Republican Party (, PRC) was a Catalanist political party during the Spanish Restoration period, that existed between 1917 and 1931 as a marger of the Autonomist Republican Bloc (BRA), the Republican Youth of Lleida (JRL) and remnants of the Republican Nationalist Federal Union (UFNR). In 1931, with the advent of the Second Spanish Republic, the party integrated itself within the newly founded Republican Left of Catalonia (ERC).
